Democratic presidential delegates have decided to vote for
Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis at the national convention,
state Senate Majority Leader Joseph Strohl said.
   ``Dukakis has proven himself to be an incredibly strong
candidate and we're very confident he's going to win the election
in November,'' Strohl said on Sunday.
