<HEAD>Stocks, Dollar Up</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with three grafs to UPDATE with closing prices; picks
up 7th pvs: Traders were...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rallied moderately in Tokyo on Monday,
while the dollar ended trading more than 1 yen higher than last
week's closing level.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, a 188.95-point winner Friday, finished Monday at
27,985.99 points, up 68.91 points or 0.24 percent.
   After opening at 133.60 yen, the U.S. dollar fell slightly to
finish the day at 133.33 yen, but still up 1.36 yen from Friday's
131.97 yen close. It traded mainly between 133.10-133.65 yen.
   Traders were believed to be reacting to improved economic
indicators in the United States, including the jobless rate, which
fell 0.3 percentage points in June.
   An exchange dealer at another commercial bank said the dollar
rose on a comment by an unidentified U.S. government official
Friday that Washington would tolerate the greenback's rise to about
135 yen.
   The dollar closed at 134.80 yen on Monday last week, its highest
closing since late November.
</TEXT>
