<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Nude Skydivers,0174</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Eight Skydive Nude At Nudist Resort</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAWSONVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight skydivers dropped in on a secluded
north Georgia resort wearing nothing but their parachutes, but
then, the several hundred people watching from below didn't have
any clothes on either.
   The nude skydiving Sunday capped a day of events at The Hidden
Valley Nudist Resort, where about 800 guests gathered in honor of
National Nude Weekend. They had several pastimes to choose from
over the weekend _ including sunbathing, camping, swimming and
volleyball _ but the skydiving demonstration was the high point of
the day.
   ``It's the first time someone has skydived nude in Georgia,''
said Evan Bell, a 61-year-old guest relations employee at the
resort.
   Eight men jumped from a plane flying at 3,500 feet, wearing only
their parachutes, and successfully landed in a field at the resort.
   One of the skydivers, Steve Smith, 38, of Fairburn, said, ``I
like the freedom of being nude. I just take my clothes off and we
go from there.''
