<DOCNO> AP880711-0076 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-07-11-88 1220EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Bomb     07-11 0124</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Bomb,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bomb Explodes When Cut In Half, Killing Three</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three people were killed and five seriously
injured when a bomb found near Shanghai exploded after a man tried
to open it with an electric saw to prove it was made of copper, an
official report said.
   The man, who had found the bomb, was trying to sell it to two
scrap metal buyers at the time of the blast. All three were killed,
the Xinmin Evening News reported in its Sunday edition, which was
seen in Beijing on Monday.
   The explosion occurred at a waste water pump station in Qingpu
county, west of Shanghai, where Sun Xuefeng, the man who found the
bomb, worked. Five spectators were seriously injured.
</TEXT>
