<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Is Michael Jackson weird?
   ``Michael knows the public thinks he's weird, strange and
unusual, but he's nothing like that,'' his sister Latoya tells
McCall's magazine in the August issue. ``That's just people's
tendencies to magnify those in the spotlight. Michael knows where
he stands, and that's what counts.''
   Again. Is Michael Jackson weird?
   ``There's a part of him that's totally pure, an inner godliness
that he protects,'' says record producer Quincy Jones. ``But the
biggest misconception about Michael is that he's weird. He's off
the wall, sure. But he's one of the most normal people I've met.
Sometimes we have to force him to get a little strange.''
   Right. But didn't he try to buy the Elephant Man's bones?
   ``Well,'' said his manager, Frank Dileo, ``everyone has a
skeleton in his closet.''
