<HEAD>U.S. Aircraft Carrier Conducts Joint Maneuvers With Israel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAIFA, Israel (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The USS Eisenhower, an aircraft carrier of
the 6th Fleet, on Monday began its first maneuvers with the Israeli
navy, the fleet commander said.
   The exercises from the northern port city will involve mock
combat at sea and refueling of the carrier by Israeli naval
vessels, the fleet commander, Vice Adm. Kendall Moranville, told
reporters.
   Moranville said the exercise will continue into next week,
following a weekend break. He would not provide other details.
   The Eisenhower, with 7,000 crew, pilots and Marines aboard,
docked at Haifa in the past but never had conducted maneuvers with
the Israelis, Moranville said. Israel has conducted naval exercises
with other ships in the 6th fleet.
   An Israeli army spokesman, in keeping with Israeli security
policy, refused to say how many Israeli troops were involved in the
operations.
