<HEAD>Prime Minister Lange Discharged from Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUCKLAND, New Zealand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister David Lange was
discharged from a hospital Tuesday morning after a 10-day stay
during which he underwent a minor heart operation.
   Lange's office issued a statement saying he would convalesce at
his Auckland home before returning to work in Wellington next week.
   Lange, 46, was admitted to Green Lane Hospital in Auckland on
July 2 after suffering chest pains.
   Doctors found a narrowing of a coronary artery and operated last
Tuesday. A surgical balloon was maneuvred to the trouble spot and
inflated, widening the artery.
   Deputy Prime Minister Geoffrey Palmer has been acting as prime
minister.
   Lange, of the Labor Party, appeared in good spirits upon leaving
the hospital and posed for photographers.
