<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Louisiana is becoming the first state to
give sales tax rebates to foreign visitors, a move designed to
boost the tourism industry and create jobs in a state plagued by
double-digit unemployment.
   The state will join 17 European countries that offer similar
refunds under a bill Gov. Buddy Roemer signed into law Friday.
   The program, which the state hopes to implement in early 1989,
will offer the rebates only for retail sales. Hotel bills, rental
cars and restaurant and bar tabs will not be affected.
</TEXT>
