prevents the issuing of separate and more powerful classes of stock
does not seriously deplete corporate America's defensive armory,
analysts say.
   Experts expect Thursday's ruling to have little impact. They
note that despite its superior ability to shield a company from
hostile bidders, supervoting stock is difficult to issue.
