<HEAD>London Stocks Little Changed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were narrowly mixed Monday as
concerns about inflation crept back into the market.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange index of 100 selected issues
was up 0.2 point, or 0.01 percent, at 1,877.4 at midday.
   Volume was light at 223 million shares, compared with 340.9
million shares at the same time Friday.
   Dealers reported a modest amount of two-way business by
institutions. The best gainers were the international stocks,
