Friday's surprisingly sharp drop in U.S. unemployment figures. The
figures depressed Wall Street late last week but left London
equities unscathed amid bullish sentiment generated by a major
order for British military equipment by Saudi Arabia.
   ``People are getting very worried the Americans are going to
start bumping up their interest rates because of inflation
worries,'' one dealer said.
   Consequently, ``we may well have to put up our interest rates to
keep sterling where we want it,'' he added.
