<2ND_LINE>BC-Northwest Fares,0210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Northwest Cuts Fares On Some Domestic Flights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines cut its lowest discount
fares in more than 500 markets, with reductions ranging from $6 to
$150 for round-trip tickets.
   Northwest also announced Monday that for a limited time it will
allow adult passengers in four cities to fly at children's prices.
Under the promotion, adult passengers who begin their trips in
Louisville, Ky.; Buffalo, N.Y.; and the Wisconsin cities of Green
Bay and Madison will be eligible for children's excursion fares on
tickets purchased in July for travel during off-peak periods
through Sept. 11.
   On a flight from Green Bay to Houston, for example, the fare
would be reduced from $348 to $158 under the promotion.
   In 500 other markets, Northwest has cut its MaxSaver fares, the
lowest discount tickets available. Northwest said the new fares
take effect immediately.
   In 17 markets, Northwest has trimmed its round-trip discount
fares by more than $100. The biggest savings is available for a
round trip between Albany, N.Y., and Tulsa, Okla., where the fare
has been cut from $368 to $218.
   Fares in nearly 300 other markets have been reduced by at least
$40. The discount fares carry restrictions.
</TEXT>
