<1ST_LINE>r f PM-PicketedUnion 1stLd-Writethru   07-11 0246</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Picketed Union, 1st Ld-Writethru,0254</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Machinists Fire Striking Secretary</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 5th graf to CORRECT to Local 971, sted District 100,
offices. Also moving on general news wires.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JUPITER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A secretary at the Machinists union local
office here said today that she has been fired after picketing the
building for almost two weeks in a contract dispute.
   Cheryl Gaal, who had worked in the union office for 12 years,
said the union's executive committee voted to dismiss her Sunday
night.
   ``They fired me for exercising my right to strike,'' said Ms.
Gaal. ``I don't think that's very smart for a labor organization.''
   Ms. Gaal had gone on strike against the Machinists to demand
more pay for performing jobs that she said were the duties of union
officials, not the office secretary. She demanded more money and an
upgrade to administrative aide, but the union refused.
   Union officers were forced to cross her solo picket line to
enter the Local 971 headquarters, which principally serves local
Pratt & Whitney employees.
   She said her own union, the Office and Professional Employees
International, had supported her strike.
   Ms. Gaal says she is looking into filing both unfair labor
practice and sex discrimination charges against the local.
   Telephone calls to the Machinist union headquarters this morning
were not answered.
   Previously, local President Fred Thorpe said it was not fair to
pay Ms. Gaal, who was earning $13.55 an hour, more than members of
the Machinists union.
</TEXT>
