<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Little Changed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing prices.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange slipped Monday
as traders awaited several British and U.S. economic reports due
this week.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 0.4
point, or 0.02 percent, to 1,876.8.
   Trading volume was 416 million shares, down from Friday's 598
million shares.
   Dealers said there was little incentive to open new positions in
advance of the economic reports. On Friday, reports are to be
releases on the British retail price index for June and the U.S.
trade figures for May.
   Until then, activity likely would remain slow, dealers said.
   ``This is a big week for indicators,'' said Jeremy Evans, market
strategist at County NatWest WoodMac in London.
</TEXT>
