<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AutoIncentives     07-11 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Incentives,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ford Extends Incentive Campaign Through Oct. 5 with Few Changes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. is extending through Oct. 5 its
buyer incentive offerings, which had been scheduled to expire on
Wednesday, the No. 2 automaker announced Monday.
   Unlike General Motors Corp., which trimmed rebates on many of
its vehicles in a similar extension two weeks ago, Ford made few
changes.
   Ford reduced rebates on the Mustang with 2.3-liter engine and
manual transmission to $500 from $750; on the Ford Taurus and
Mercury Sable to $500 from $600; and on Ford Tempo and Mercury
Topaz to $400 from $500.
   Other rebates _ ranging from $300 on Ranger S compact pickup
trucks, Festiva and 1988 Ford Escort, to $1,000 on Ford Thunderbird
Turbo Coupe and Mercury XR-7 _ remain unchanged.
   Ford said it was continuing the incentive program to keep its
dealers competitive but noted that sales were strong and
inventories low on many models.
</TEXT>
